The Ministry of Education has invited applications from form four leavers to be trained as P1 primary school teachers.A statement signed by Basic Education PS Belio Kipsang said applicants must have attained a KCSE mean grade of C.&ldquo;Those with special needs are also encouraged to register,&rdquo; said the statement.Those with visual and hearing impairments should have a mean grade of C-.Eligible applicants should personally submit registration forms at the zonal education offices between April 10 and May 3.Registration forms can be downloaded from the Education ministry&rsquo;s website - www.education.go.ke - free of charge.&ldquo;Admission letters for the successful candidates for both first and second admissions will be dispatched to the zonal education offices, not posted,&rdquo; the statement reads.Last year, the government recruited 10,901 applicants into teacher training colleges.Teacher shortages in public schools stood at 87,489 in October last year, with the deficit in primary schools standing at 39,913.Education CS Fred Matiang&rsquo;i (pictured) told the National Assembly Committee on Education only six counties have a sufficient number of primary school teachers.They are Nyamira, Kiambu, Kirinyaga, Kisii, Murang&rsquo;a and Nyeri.To address the shortage, Knut demanded the government hire an additional 90,000 teachers.